### optional
``` bash
  sudo apt install \
    pipx \
    qemu-system \
    libfirt-daemon-system \
    virt-manager \
    wdisplays \
    emacs \
    
    
    # not sure if required \
    net-tools \
    pulseaudio-utils \
    libspa-0.2-bluetooth # https://askubuntu.com/a/1480049 \
```

- generate ssh key
``` bash
  git remote set-url origin git@github.com:alvaronaschez/df.git
```

- this is needed so virt-manager works properly
```
sudo usermod -aG libvirt $USER && sudo usermod -aG kvm $USER
```

- add opendns to the following file
```
sudo vi /etc/resolv.conf
```
it doesn't work because of NetworkManager
do this instead:
add the dns using nmtui and then:
``` bash
service NetworkManager restart
```

